rComments: I had a bad experience taking this class. If you can avoid taking it, do. She is incredibly unclear in her grading criteria and assignment instructions. She contradicts herself constantly and leaves out crucial information to aid in success. She is very inappropriate and lacks professionalism. This class caused me so much stress and anxiety.

Really disappointing course. The level of condescension included in the feedback isn't helpful and took all of my motivation to actually try/learn. Super easy to get a solid grade - almost impossible to get 85+. If you take a lot of pride in your work and really strive to get high grades, you might not want to take a course with this professor.

her feedback just doesn't make sense, very rude with the feedback and when you do what she says she still complains and is very passive-aggressive. the quizzes are pretty easy but there's an assignment after every class for participation marks which aren' too hard. overall not that hard of a class but her grading sucks and not compassionate at all.
I LOVE HER YES!!!! Go off Marlene! Love her family and her! Take her you wont regret!
I LOVE HER WITH ALL MY HEART  BEST PROF EVER!
Marlene Lundy was amazing just get close to her and read her feedback and it's an easy A.

She is one of the best people I have ever dealt with. She has the best personality and her way of teaching was very inspiring. I adore her. I took two English as a second language courses with her in 2004.

Definitely need to go to class. But she's very clear about what she expects from each assignment, so as long as you take notes when she goes through her marking scheme you'll do fine. She does drag on a little bit when she's talking (something that engineering students aren't used to in a prof), but just be patient and hand in your assignments.
Provides good feedback and wants you to succeed
This teacher won't let you pass because she gave very difficult quiz.
didnt like the course or her for that matter.
the greatest professor ever

Worst prof I have ever had she over explains EVERY single thing even when you try to ask a question she doesn't take the time to eve listen to you instead she will go on her own monologue and often talk about her life. the work load is way too heavy humm hello I case you didn't notice its not the only class that I am taking!

She is horrible.  She over explains everything so much so that you no longer understand.  She is very unprofessional when addressing issues with students.  She is full of herself and addresses more about her family than she does about the course information.

In terms of course material, there was very little but she explained it well enough in a clear manner. If you are good at explaining basic engineering concepts to less technical people, this class should be easy for you. You don't need to do her reading assignments. If I had to take this class again, I would definitely have her again.

For someone with a PhD in "professional communication" this prof behaves like a high school student. She looks as if she didn't have the talent for low-budget theatre so she decided to major in "pretending to be a professional".  She's full of herself and doesn't't stop talking about her ambassador husband. Please find a new prof for this course !!

This lady is probably the worst professor I have ever had.  She spends more time flirting with students in the class than she does teaching.  I'm not even sure why she's there as the class revolves around group work and assignments.  It seems her only job is trying to explain her ridiculously intricate course outline.   My Math course is less work!

Expectations in her courses are always very clear and it is easy to do well. As per faculty regulations, A+ grading is not given out unless there are extraordinary circumstances. She has a lot of knowledge in the field, though tends to revert to ESL teacher form rather than grad form if there are international students in the class.

I cant understand why she looks popular around students.Maybe it is because the assignments are not much. If you are interested in her personal stories, go ahead, but if you are expecting some professional and smart talk...
Good Professor
